// =============================================================================
// core.architecture — ATS-V Architectural Type System library (Сезон 1)
// =============================================================================
//
// **Verum-native canonical types for the Architectural Type System.**
//
// Per `internal/specs/ats-v.md` §17.4 (Reuse compliance), the ATS-V
// extension is implemented as:
//
//   1. ONE typed attribute — `@arch_module(...)` — recognised by the
//      compiler-internal dispatch (V8.1 META1 architectural principle,
//      grammar/verum.ebnf:438 generic identifier(args) form).
//
//   2. THIS library — Verum-native `type X is variant_list` declarations
//      that mirror the kernel-side `verum_kernel::arch` primitives.
//      Both sides stay in sync via cross-side pin tests.
//
//   3. Library theorems in `anti_patterns.vr` declaring kernel-discharge
//      bridges for the 10 canonical anti-patterns (Сезон 1; Сезон 2 lands
//      remaining 22).
//
// **Architectural alignment** mirrors `core.verify.separation_soundness`
// (#161) and `core.verify.codegen_soundness` (#162): kernel-discharge
// pattern with `@kernel_discharge(<intrinsic>)` annotations.
//
// **Module roster** (Сезон 1):
//
//   1. `types.vr` — canonical primitives (Capability / Boundary /
//      Composition / Lifecycle / Foundation / Tier / MsfsStratum /
//      CveClosure / Shape).
//   2. `capability_ontology.vr` — registered Custom capability names.
//   3. `anti_patterns.vr` — 10 canonical anti-pattern theorems with
//      stable error codes ATS-V-AP-001..010.
//
// **Future modules** (Сезон 2-3):
//   * `composition_algebra.vr` — explicit composition operators.
//   * `mtac_operators.vr` — modal-temporal calculus (§20-§23 spec).
//   * `counterfactual.vr` — type-only what-if reasoning (§22 spec).
// =============================================================================

module core.architecture.mod;

mount super.types.{
    Capability,
    Boundary,
    Lifecycle,
    Foundation,
    Tier,
    MsfsStratum,
    CveClosure,
    Shape,
};
mount super.anti_patterns.{
    kernel_arch_capability_discipline,
    kernel_arch_boundary_check,
    kernel_arch_composition_check,
    kernel_arch_lifecycle_check,
    kernel_arch_foundation_consistency,
    kernel_arch_anti_pattern_check,
    kernel_arch_cve_closure,
    kernel_arch_soundness_v0,
};
